[{"text": "Today I want to talk to you", "start": 15.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about ethnic conflict", "start": 17.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and civil war.", "start": 19.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "These are not normally the most cheerful of topics,", "start": 21.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "nor do they generally generate", "start": 24.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the kind of good news", "start": 26.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that this conference is about.", "start": 28.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yet, not only is there at least some good news", "start": 31.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to be told about fewer such conflicts now", "start": 34.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "than two decades ago,", "start": 37.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but what is perhaps more important", "start": 39.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that we also have come", "start": 41.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to a much better understanding of what can be done", "start": 43.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to further reduce the number", "start": 46.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of ethnic conflicts and civil wars", "start": 48.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the suffering that they inflict.", "start": 51.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Three things stand out:", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "leadership, diplomacy", "start": 56.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and institutional design.", "start": 59.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What I will focus on in my talk", "start": 62.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is why they matter, how they matter,", "start": 64.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and what we can all do", "start": 67.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make sure that they continue to matter", "start": 69.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the right ways,", "start": 71.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that is, how all of us can contribute", "start": 73.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to developing and honing the skills", "start": 76.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of local and global leaders", "start": 79.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to make peace", "start": 82.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to make it last.", "start": 84.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But let's start at the beginning.", "start": 86.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Civil wars have made news headlines", "start": 89.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for many decades now,", "start": 91.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and ethnic conflicts in particular", "start": 93.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have been a near constant presence", "start": 95.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as a major international security threat.", "start": 98.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For nearly two decades now,", "start": 101.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the news has been bad", "start": 104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the images have been haunting.", "start": 106.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In Georgia, after years of stalemate,", "start": 109.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we saw a full-scale resurgence of violence", "start": 112.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in August, 2008.", "start": 115.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This quickly escalated into a five-day war", "start": 117.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between Russia and Georgia,", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "leaving Georgia ever more divided.", "start": 122.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In Kenya, contested presidential elections in 2007 --", "start": 125.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we just heard about them --", "start": 128.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "quickly led to high levels", "start": 131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of inter-ethnic violence", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the killing and displacement", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of thousands of people.", "start": 137.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In Sri Lanka,", "start": 139.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a decades-long civil war", "start": 141.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between the Tamil minority", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the Sinhala majority", "start": 145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "led to a bloody climax in 2009,", "start": 147.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "after perhaps as many as 100,000", "start": 150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "people had been killed", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "since 1983.", "start": 154.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In Kyrgyzstan, just over the last few weeks,", "start": 156.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "unprecedented levels of violence occurred", "start": 159.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "between ethnic Kyrgyz", "start": 162.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and ethnic Uzbeks.", "start": 164.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Hundreds have been killed,", "start": 166.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and more than 100,000 displaced,", "start": 168.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "including many ethnic Uzbeks", "start": 171.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who fled to neighboring Uzbekistan.", "start": 173.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the Middle East,", "start": 176.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "conflict between Israelis and Palestinians", "start": 178.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "continues unabated,", "start": 181.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it becomes ever more difficult", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to see how, just how", "start": 185.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a possible, sustainable solution", "start": 188.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can be achieved.", "start": 190.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Darfur may have slipped from the news headlines,", "start": 193.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but the killing and displacement there", "start": 196.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "continues as well,", "start": 198.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the sheer human misery that it creates", "start": 200.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is very hard to fathom.", "start": 203.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And in Iraq, finally,", "start": 205.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "violence is on the rise again,", "start": 207.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the country has yet to form a government", "start": 210.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "four months after", "start": 213.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "its last parliamentary elections.", "start": 215.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But hang on, this talk is to be about the good news.", "start": 220.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So are these now the images of the past?", "start": 223.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, notwithstanding the gloomy pictures", "start": 227.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from the Middle East, Darfur,", "start": 230.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Iraq, elsewhere,", "start": 232.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is a longer-term trend", "start": 234.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that does represent some good news.", "start": 236.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Over the past two decades, since the end of the Cold War,", "start": 239.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "there has been an overall decline", "start": 242.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the number of civil wars.", "start": 245.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Since the high in the early 1990s,", "start": 247.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with about 50 such civil wars ongoing,", "start": 250.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we now have 30 percent fewer", "start": 253.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "such conflicts today.", "start": 255.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The number of people killed in civil wars", "start": 257.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "also is much lower today", "start": 259.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "than it was a decade ago or two.", "start": 262.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But this trend is less unambiguous.", "start": 265.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The highest level of deaths on the battlefield", "start": 268.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was recorded between 1998 and 2001,", "start": 271.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with about 80,000 soldiers, policemen and rebels", "start": 274.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "killed every year.", "start": 277.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The lowest number of combatant casualties", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "occurred in 2003,", "start": 281.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with just 20,000 killed.", "start": 284.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Despite the up and down since then,", "start": 287.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the overall trend --", "start": 290.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and this is the important bit --", "start": 292.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "clearly points downward", "start": 294.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the past two decades.", "start": 296.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The news about civilian casualties", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is also less bad than it used to be.", "start": 301.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "From over 12,000 civilians", "start": 303.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "deliberately killed in civil wars", "start": 305.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in 1997 and 1998,", "start": 307.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a decade later,", "start": 310.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this figure stands at 4,000.", "start": 312.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a decrease by two-thirds.", "start": 315.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This decline would be even more obvious", "start": 318.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we factored in the genocide in Rwanda", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in 1994.", "start": 322.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But then 800,000 civilians were slaughtered", "start": 324.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in a matter of just a few months.", "start": 327.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This certainly is an accomplishment", "start": 330.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that must never be surpassed.", "start": 332.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What is also important is to note", "start": 335.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that these figures only tell part of the story.", "start": 337.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They exclude people", "start": 340.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that died as a consequence of civil war,", "start": 342.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from hunger or disease, for example.", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And they also do not properly account", "start": 346.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for civilian suffering more generally.", "start": 348.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Torture, rape and ethnic cleansing", "start": 352.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "have become highly effective,", "start": 355.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "if often non-lethal, weapons in civil war.", "start": 358.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "To put it differently,", "start": 362.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the civilians that suffer the consequences", "start": 364.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of ethnic conflict and civil war,", "start": 367.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "there is no good war", "start": 370.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and there is no bad peace.", "start": 373.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thus, even though every civilian killed,", "start": 377.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "maimed, raped, or tortured is one too many,", "start": 379.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the fact that the number", "start": 382.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of civilian casualties", "start": 384.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is clearly lower today", "start": 386.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than it was a decade ago,", "start": 388.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is good news.", "start": 390.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So, we have fewer conflicts today", "start": 393.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in which fewer people get killed.", "start": 395.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the big question, of course,", "start": 398.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is why?", "start": 400.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "In some cases,", "start": 402.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is a military victory of one side.", "start": 404.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is a solution of sorts,", "start": 406.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but rarely is it one", "start": 408.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that comes without human costs", "start": 410.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or humanitarian consequences.", "start": 412.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The defeat of the Tamil Tigers in Sri Lanka", "start": 415.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is perhaps the most recent example of this,", "start": 418.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but we have seen similar", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so-called military solutions", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the Balkans, in the South Caucasus", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and across most of Africa.", "start": 427.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "At times, they are complimented", "start": 430.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by negotiated settlements,", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or at least cease-fire agreements,", "start": 434.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and peacekeepers are deployed.", "start": 436.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But hardly ever do they represent", "start": 438.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a resounding success --", "start": 440.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Bosnia and Herzegovina", "start": 442.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "perhaps more so than Georgia.", "start": 444.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But for many parts of Africa,", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a colleague of mine once put it this way,", "start": 448.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"The cease-fire on Tuesday night", "start": 451.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was reached just in time", "start": 454.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the genocide to start on Wednesday morning.\"", "start": 456.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But let's look at the good news again.", "start": 461.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If there's no solution on the battlefield,", "start": 463.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "three factors can account", "start": 465.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the prevention of ethnic conflict and civil war,", "start": 467.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "or for sustainable peace afterwards:", "start": 471.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "leadership, diplomacy", "start": 474.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and institutional design.", "start": 476.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Take the example of Northern Ireland.", "start": 479.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Despite centuries of animosity,", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "decades of violence", "start": 484.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and thousands of people killed,", "start": 486.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "1998 saw the conclusion", "start": 489.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of an historic agreement.", "start": 491.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Its initial version was skillfully mediated", "start": 494.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by Senator George Mitchell.", "start": 497.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Crucially, for the long-term success", "start": 499.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the peace process in Northern Ireland,", "start": 501.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "he imposed very clear conditions", "start": 504.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the participation and negotiations.", "start": 506.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Central among them,", "start": 509.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a commitment", "start": 511.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to exclusively peaceful means.", "start": 513.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Subsequent revisions of the agreement", "start": 516.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were facilitated by the British and Irish governments,", "start": 518.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who never wavered in their determination", "start": 521.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to bring peace and stability to Northern Ireland.", "start": 524.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The core institutions", "start": 527.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that were put in place in 1998", "start": 529.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and their modifications", "start": 531.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in 2006 and 2008", "start": 533.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "were highly innovative", "start": 535.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and allowed all conflict parties", "start": 537.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to see their core concerns and demands addressed.", "start": 540.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The agreement combines a power-sharing arrangement", "start": 544.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Northern Ireland", "start": 546.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with cross-border institutions", "start": 548.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that link Belfast and Dublin", "start": 550.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and thus recognizes", "start": 552.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the so-called Irish dimension of the conflict.", "start": 554.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And significantly,", "start": 557.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there's also a clear focus", "start": 559.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on both the rights of individuals", "start": 561.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the rights of communities.", "start": 563.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The provisions in the agreement may be complex,", "start": 567.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but so is the underlying conflict.", "start": 570.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Perhaps most importantly,", "start": 574.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "local leaders repeatedly rose to the challenge of compromise,", "start": 576.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "not always fast", "start": 580.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and not always enthusiastically,", "start": 582.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but rise in the end they did.", "start": 585.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Who ever could have imagined", "start": 587.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Ian Paisley and Martin McGuinness", "start": 590.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "jointly governing Northern Ireland", "start": 593.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as First and Deputy First Minister?", "start": 595.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But then, is Northern Ireland a unique example,", "start": 598.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or does this kind of explanation", "start": 601.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "only hold more generally", "start": 603.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in democratic and developed countries?", "start": 605.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "By no means.", "start": 608.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The ending of Liberia's long-lasting civil war", "start": 610.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in 2003", "start": 613.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "illustrates the importance", "start": 615.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of leadership, diplomacy", "start": 617.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and institutional design", "start": 619.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as much as the successful prevention", "start": 621.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of a full-scale civil war", "start": 623.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Macedonia in 2001,", "start": 625.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or the successful ending", "start": 628.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the conflict in Aceh in Indonesia in 2005.", "start": 630.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In all three cases,", "start": 634.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "local leaders were willing and able", "start": 636.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make peace,", "start": 638.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the international community stood ready", "start": 640.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to help them negotiate and implement an agreement,", "start": 643.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the institutions have lived up", "start": 646.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to the promise that they held", "start": 649.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on the day they were agreed.", "start": 651.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Focusing on leadership, diplomacy", "start": 653.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and institutional design", "start": 655.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "also helps explain failures to achieve peace,", "start": 657.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or to make it last.", "start": 660.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The hopes that were vested in the Oslo Accords", "start": 662.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "did not lead to an end", "start": 664.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the Israeli/Palestinian conflict.", "start": 666.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Not all the issues that needed to be resolved", "start": 668.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were actually covered in the agreements.", "start": 671.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Rather, local leaders committed", "start": 673.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to revisiting them later on.", "start": 676.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yet instead of grasping this opportunity,", "start": 679.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "local and international leaders", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "soon disengaged", "start": 683.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and became distracted", "start": 685.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the second Intifada, the events of 9/11", "start": 687.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the wars in Afghanistan and Iraq.", "start": 690.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The comprehensive peace agreement for Sudan", "start": 694.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "signed in 2005", "start": 696.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "turned out to be less comprehensive than envisaged,", "start": 698.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and its provisions may yet bear the seeds", "start": 701.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of a full-scale return to war", "start": 704.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between north and south.", "start": 706.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Changes and shortcomings in leadership,", "start": 708.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "more off than on international diplomacy", "start": 711.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and institutional failures", "start": 714.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "account for this", "start": 716.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in almost equal measure.", "start": 718.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Unresolved boundary issues, squabbles over oil revenues,", "start": 720.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the ongoing conflict in Darfur,", "start": 723.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "escalating tribal violence in the south", "start": 725.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and generally weak state capacity", "start": 728.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "across all of Sudan", "start": 730.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "complete a very depressing picture", "start": 732.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the state of affairs", "start": 735.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Africa's largest country.", "start": 737.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "A final example: Kosovo.", "start": 739.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The failure to achieve", "start": 741.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a negotiated solution for Kosovo", "start": 743.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the violence, tension", "start": 745.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and de facto partition that resulted from it", "start": 747.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "have their reasons", "start": 750.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in many, many different factors.", "start": 752.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Central among them are three.", "start": 755.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "First, the intransigence of local leaders", "start": 758.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to settle for nothing less", "start": 761.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than their maximum demands.", "start": 763.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Second, an international diplomatic effort", "start": 766.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that was hampered from the beginning", "start": 769.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by Western support for Kosovo's independence.", "start": 772.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And third, a lack of imagination", "start": 776.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "when it came to designing institutions", "start": 779.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that could have addressed the concerns", "start": 782.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of Serbs and Albanians alike.", "start": 784.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "By the same token --", "start": 787.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and here we have some good news again --", "start": 789.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the very fact that there is a high-level,", "start": 791.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "well-resourced international presence", "start": 794.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Kosovo", "start": 796.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and the Balkans region more generally", "start": 798.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the fact that local leaders on both sides", "start": 801.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have showed relative restraint,", "start": 803.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "explains why things have not been worse", "start": 805.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "over the past two years since 2008.", "start": 808.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So even in situations", "start": 811.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where outcomes are less than optimal,", "start": 813.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "local leaders", "start": 816.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and international leaders have a choice,", "start": 818.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and they can make a difference for the better.", "start": 821.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A cold war", "start": 824.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is not as good", "start": 826.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as a cold peace,", "start": 828.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but a cold peace", "start": 830.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is still better than a hot war.", "start": 832.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Good news is also about learning the right lesson.", "start": 836.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So what then distinguishes", "start": 839.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the Israeli/Palestinian conflict", "start": 841.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from that in Northern Ireland,", "start": 843.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or the civil war in Sudan", "start": 846.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from that in Liberia?", "start": 848.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Both successes and failures", "start": 850.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "teach us several critically important things", "start": 853.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that we need to bear in mind", "start": 856.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if we want the good news to continue.", "start": 858.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "First, leadership.", "start": 860.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the same way in which ethnic conflict and civil war", "start": 863.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "are not natural", "start": 867.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but man-made disasters,", "start": 869.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "their prevention and settlement", "start": 871.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "does not happen automatically either.", "start": 873.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Leadership needs to be capable,", "start": 877.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "determined and visionary", "start": 880.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in its commitment to peace.", "start": 882.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Leaders need to connect to each other", "start": 884.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and to their followers,", "start": 887.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and they need to bring them along", "start": 889.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on what is an often arduous journey", "start": 891.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "into a peaceful future.", "start": 894.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Second, diplomacy.", "start": 896.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Diplomacy needs to be well resourced,", "start": 899.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "sustained,", "start": 902.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and apply the right mix of incentives and pressures", "start": 904.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on leaders and followers.", "start": 906.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It needs to help them reach an equitable compromise,", "start": 908.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and it needs to ensure", "start": 911.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that a broad coalition", "start": 913.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of local, regional", "start": 915.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and international supporters", "start": 917.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "help them implement their agreement.", "start": 919.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Third, institutional design.", "start": 922.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Institutional design requires", "start": 925.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a keen focus on issues,", "start": 927.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "innovative thinking", "start": 929.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and flexible and well-funded implementation.", "start": 931.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Conflict parties need to move away", "start": 935.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from maximum demands", "start": 938.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and towards a compromise", "start": 940.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that recognizes each other's needs.", "start": 942.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they need to think", "start": 945.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the substance of their agreement", "start": 947.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "much more than about", "start": 949.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the labels they want to attach to them.", "start": 951.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Conflict parties also need to be prepared", "start": 953.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to return to the negotiation table", "start": 955.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "if the agreement implementation stalls.", "start": 958.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For me personally,", "start": 962.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the most critical lesson of all is this:", "start": 964.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Local commitment to peace", "start": 967.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is all-important,", "start": 969.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but it is often not enough", "start": 971.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to prevent or end violence.", "start": 974.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Yet, no amount of diplomacy", "start": 977.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or institutional design", "start": 980.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "can make up for local failures", "start": 982.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the consequences that they have.", "start": 985.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Therefore, we must invest", "start": 988.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in developing leaders,", "start": 991.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "leaders that have the skills,", "start": 994.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "vision and determination", "start": 997.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to make peace.", "start": 999.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Leaders, in other words,", "start": 1001.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that people will trust", "start": 1003.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and that they will want to follow", "start": 1005.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "even if that means", "start": 1008.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "making hard choices.", "start": 1010.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A final thought:", "start": 1013.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Ending civil wars", "start": 1015.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a process that is fraught with dangers,", "start": 1017.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "frustrations and setbacks.", "start": 1020.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It often takes a generation to accomplish,", "start": 1023.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but it also requires us, today's generation,", "start": 1026.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to take responsibility", "start": 1029.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and to learn the right lessons", "start": 1031.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about leadership, diplomacy", "start": 1033.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and institutional design,", "start": 1036.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so that the child soldiers of today", "start": 1039.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "can become the children of tomorrow.", "start": 1042.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1044.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1046.26, "duration": 3.0}]